Catch Yourself: 
Be aware of when youâ€™re stuck in your thoughts and try to shift your focus.

Find a Distraction:
 Engage in an activity you enjoy to divert your mind.

Take a Deep Breath: 
Deep breathing can help calm your mind and body.

Meditate:
 Regular meditation can help clear your mind and reduce overthinking.

Look at the Bigger Picture:
 Try to view your situation from a broader perspective.

Be Kind to Yourself: 
Treat yourself with the same compassion you would offer to a friend.

Acknowledge Your Successes: 
Instead of dwelling on your mistakes, focus on your achievements.

Stay Present: 
Try to keep your mind focused on the present moment.

Consider Other Viewpoints: 
Try to see the situation from other perspectives.

Take Action: 
Instead of thinking about what you could do, take steps to do it.
